INSTALLATION

To install QBXSBC:

    QuickBASIC 4.50 users:

        To get a QLB for the environment:

        C>link /qu QBXSBC1N.LIB,QBXSBC1N.QLB,nul,bqlb45.lib

        (4.00, 4.00b users change bqlb45 to blqb40, bqlb41.)

        To link to a completed program (stand-alone):

        C>bc yourprg.bas /o;
        C>link yourprg.obj,yourprg.exe,nul,QBXSBC1N.LIB


    BASIC 7.1 users:

        To get a QLB for the environment:

        C>link /qu QBXSBC1F.LIB,QBXSBC1F.QLB,nul,qbxqlb.lib

        To link to a completed program (stand-alone):

        C>bc yourprg.bas /o/fs;
        C>link yourprg.obj,yourprg.exe,nul,QBXSBC1F.LIB;


To install SOUND.COM, SB-SOUND.COM:

        C>SOUND
        C>SOUND [/Pxxx,][/Bxx]
           where xxx = base port address (default 0388h)
                  xx = size of event buffer in K (1-64)

        C>SB-SOUND
        C>SB-SOUND [/Pxxx,][/Bxx]
           where xxx = base port address (default 0220h/0388h)
                  xx = size of event buffer in K (1-64)
        C>SB-SOUND /u
           to uninstall the sound driver (SB-SOUND only)


